â“ Concept Questions (Important)
ğŸ”¹ Where are logs stored?
/var/log

ğŸ§  Why /var/log?

/var = variable data

Logs constantly change

So Linux stores logs in /var/log

Examples:

/var/log/syslog
/var/log/auth.log

ğŸ”¹ Which directory works like RAM?
/tmp

ğŸ§  Why /tmp?

Temporary storage

Files auto-deleted on reboot

Similar behavior to RAM

âœ… Summary

SSH â†’ remote login

ls -a â†’ hidden files

rm -R â†’ delete directories

file â†’ detect file type

Permissions â†’ rwx

Logs â†’ /var/log

